Notes:
What this Makefile does
Compilation
- Compiles your hybrid_demo.c
- Compiles all required Kyber reference .c files
- Includes the Kyber header directory (-Ikyber/ref)
- Optimizes with -O3 and enables warnings
Linking
- Links against libsodium, which provides X25519/ECDHE and hashing
Output
- Produces a single executable: hybrid_demo
Cleanup
- make clean removes the binary and any .o files

Project Structure:

project/
│
├── hybrid_demo.c
└── kyber/
    └── ref/
        ├── api.h
        ├── kem.c
        ├── indcpa.c
        ├── poly.c
        ├── ntt.c
        ├── reduce.c
        ├── symmetric-shake.c
        └── (other Kyber ref files)
		
A Makefile that reliably builds your hybrid Kyber + ECDHE demo needs to do three things cleanly:

- Compile all required Kyber ref sources
- Compile your hybrid_demo.c
- Link everything with -lsodium
